<center><font size=7><b>Tau Ceti 2: Academy</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 2</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>In the 'If It Moves' scenario, play exactly like Tau Ceti, in other words
edge forward and use scanner.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In 'Red Dawn', use the same tactics as above but use bomb on factories.  In
'Meltdown', put on your Elite uniform and Go For It!  You'd better be a
darn good combatter, though.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In 'Softly, Softly' the mines form a kind of Race Track - watch out for the
irregularly spaced ones, 'cos they're not mines, they're 'thingies'!<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't move along the spoke in 'Cipher' - attack at&nbsp;right angles and use Tau
Ceti tactics.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In the 'OK Corral' scenario, use Tau Ceti again, but use missiles on small
and 'Sid Vicious' meanies.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In 'Where To Guv?' don't, repeat, don't use the jump pads!  Since
navigation is awful, go West, then East, then slightly South to get to the
action.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Finally, in 'Hide And Seek' use Suppressor Droids (spinning tops) to stop
the discs firing.  Use bombs to destroy them.
 <i>(Andrew Cope in Your Sinclair issue 15)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Multiface pokes</i></b></font></td></tr>
